    <sec id="Sec8">
      <title>Document ranking functions</title>
      <p id="Par56">A2A’s experimental setup offers a choice between two document ranking functions: Divergence from Randomness (DFR) [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR26">26</xref>] and Okapi Best Match 25 (BM25) [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR27">27</xref>]. This choice dictates which mechanism is used to calculate the document relevance. That is, it determines the way the final document ranking is produced by Solr search engine.</p>
      <p id="Par57">Inclusion of BM25 is due to the method’s status as a <italic>de facto</italic> standard in IR. BM25 constitutes a strong baseline, which often outperforms elaborate ranking strategies [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR28">28</xref>]. Our choice of the second method, DFR, has been influenced by its high effectiveness reported for biomedical search [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR29">29</xref>, <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR30">30</xref>].</p>
      <p id="Par58">BM25 is a refined variant of Term Frequency-Inverse Document Frequency (TF-IDF). The core idea of BM25 is that documents should be assigned higher scores the more important terms (words) of the query they contain, where the importance of an individual term is modeled by its inverse document frequency (so, an inverse of how common it is in the entire corpus). Formally, given a query <italic>Q</italic> (again, a bag) with terms <inline-formula id="IEq17"><alternatives><tex-math id="M37">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$t_1, t_2, ..., t_n$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M38"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mo>.</mml:mo><mml:mo>.</mml:mo><mml:mo>.</mml:mo><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mi>n</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2020_3894_Article_IEq17.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, the BM25 score of a document <italic>D</italic> is given by<disp-formula id="Equ3"><label>3</label><alternatives><tex-math id="M39">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} BM25(D, Q) = \sum _{i=1}^{n} IDF (t_i) \cdot \frac{f(t_i, D) \cdot (k_1 + 1)}{f(t_i, D) + k_1 \cdot (1 - b + b \cdot \frac{|D|}{avgdl})}, \end{aligned}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M40" display="block"><mml:mrow><mml:mtable><mml:mtr><mml:mtd columnalign="right"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>B</mml:mi><mml:mi>M</mml:mi><mml:mn>25</mml:mn><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>D</mml:mi><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mi>Q</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:munderover><mml:mo>∑</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mi>n</mml:mi></mml:munderover><mml:mi>I</mml:mi><mml:mi>D</mml:mi><mml:mi>F</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mo>·</mml:mo><mml:mfrac><mml:mrow><mml:mi>f</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mi>D</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mo>·</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>k</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>f</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mi>D</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>k</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>·</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mo>-</mml:mo><mml:mi>b</mml:mi><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:mi>b</mml:mi><mml:mo>·</mml:mo><mml:mfrac><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">|</mml:mo><mml:mi>D</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">|</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">avgdl</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfrac><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:mrow></mml:mfrac><mml:mo>,</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:mtd></mml:mtr></mml:mtable></mml:mrow></mml:math><graphic xlink:href="12859_2020_3894_Article_Equ3.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula>where <inline-formula id="IEq18"><alternatives><tex-math id="M41">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$f(t_i, D)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M42"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>f</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mi>D</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2020_3894_Article_IEq18.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> denotes the raw frequency of term <inline-formula id="IEq19"><alternatives><tex-math id="M43">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
