      <sec id="Sec14">
        <title>Use case 2: adding ‘solid’ to cancer queries</title>
        <p id="Par87">In our use case 2, we present an evaluation of a widely adopted approach of reformulating TREC PM queries for clinical trials retrieval by adding terms ‘solid tumor’ with a lower term weight for topics regarding non-blood cancers [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR32">32</xref>, <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR33">33</xref>]. We use the expansion weight of 0.2. We evaluate both abstract and clinical trial retrieval tasks. We add the expansion term only to topics which do not contain the word ‘leukemia’ (as leukemia is not a solid tumor cancer). We also skip the expansion for the last 10 topics of the 2019 topic set (as these are diseases other than cancers, so no solid tumors altogether). The pseudocode for the procedure is as follows (a Python implementation and reformulated topics can be found in the Resources page):</p>
        <graphic position="anchor" xlink:href="12859_2020_3894_Figc_HTML" id="MO13"/>
